/wiki/Cycling_at_the_2011_Parapan_Americ: Cycling was contested at the 2011 Parapan American Games from November 13 to 19 at the Pan American Velodrome in Guadalajara, Mexico. Road cycling events were held on November 13 and 19, while track cycling events were held on November 15 and 16.
/wiki/Amanda_Everlove: Amanda Everlove (born 1988 or 1989) is an American Paralympic swimmer.
/wiki/Swimming_at_the_2011_Parapan_Ameri: Swimming will be contested at the 2011 Parapan American Games from November 13 to 19 at the Scotiabank Aquatics Center in Guadalajara, Mexico.
/wiki/Anna_Johannes: Anna Johannes (born 1993) is an American Paralympic swimmer.
/wiki/Jarryd_Wallace: Jarryd Wallace (born May 15, 1990) is an American T44 Paralympic sprint runner who won the 100 m event at the 2011 and 2015 Parapan American Games. He is a student in sport management at the University of Georgia.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2011_Parapan_Amer: Athletics contests were held at the 2011 Parapan American Games from November 14 to 20 at the Telmex Athletics Stadium in Guadalajara, Mexico.
/wiki/Scott_Winkler_(athlete): Scott Winkler is an American Paralympic track and field athlete who competes in men's shot put.
/wiki/David_Prince: David Prince (born 10 September 1983) is a USA sprint runner who runs in the T44 class. He was raised by missionary parents and traveled frequently, living for a while in Oaxaca, Mexico. He lost his right leg below the knee in a motorcycle accident in 2002.
/wiki/Amberlynn_Weber: Amberlynn Weber (born 1993) is an American Paralympic track and fielder. At the 2011 Parapan American Games, she won gold medals in 100 m, 400 m, and 800 m and a bronze medal in 200 m.
/wiki/Raymond_Martin_(athlete): Raymond Martin (born January 2, 1992) is a Filipino/Irish-American Paralympic athlete.  He won four gold medals at the 2012 Summer Paralympic Games in the T52 wheelchair racing category.
/wiki/Chelsea_McClammer: Chelsea McClammer (born March 1, 1994) is an American Track and Field athlete. With Team USA, she has won two silver medals and one bronze at the 2016 Summer Paralympics.
/wiki/Zena_Cole: Zena Cole is an American Paralympic discus thrower.
/wiki/Jennifer_Schuble: Jennifer Schuble (born July 8, 1976 in Lake Charles, Louisiana) is an American track and road cyclist.
/wiki/Tahl_Leibovitz: Tahl Leibovitz (born June 1, 1975) is an American para table tennis player who has played in five Paralympic Games. His highest ranking is world no.2 in class 9 in July 2008 and is now currently ranked world no.3 in that class and world no.17 in men's standing classes.
/wiki/Table_tennis_at_the_2011_Parapan_A: Table tennis was contested at the 2011 Parapan American Games from November 13 to 18 at the CODE II Gymnasium in Guadalajara, Mexico.
